From: finaid@msoe.edu<mailto:finaid@msoe.edu> [mailto:finaid@msoe.edu] Sent: Friday, May 20, 2016 11:08 AM To: Hill, Thomas <hillt@msoe.edu<mailto:hillt@msoe.edu>> Subject: MSOE Financial Aid - Your 2016-2017 Award Offer is Available
Student ID: 541098
Dear Thomas:
The MSOE Financial Aid Office has received your processed FAFSA and is pleased to offer financial aid to assist you in meeting your educational expenses for the 2016-2017 academic year.
To view your award offer, please visit http://myfinancialaid.msoe.edu. You will need your MSOE user name and password to login.
IMPORTANT NOTE: In order to access your financial aid information, please register<https://community.msoe.edu/welcome> your @msoe.edu account on the MSOE Community site if you have not already done so. This process creates a link via Single Sign On from your @msoe.edu account to myFinancialAid.
Authentication takes place behind the firewall and no passwords are stored on the MSOE Community.
For your reference, the “Claiming Your Financial Aid Award” brochure under the Forms & Resources section on your “My Financial Aid” site can assist with many frequently asked questions. Please read and carefully follow the instructions in the brochure.
Your award is based on the following enrollment levels: Full-time for the Fall term Full-time for the Winter term Full-time for the Spring term.
If your enrollment level changes, we asked that you notify the Financial Aid Office so that we may adjustment your award offer to reflect your enrollment status, if necessary.
If you wish to adjust any previously accepted/declined aid listed online, please use our online form at: www.msoe.edu/accept-your-award<http://www.msoe.edu/accept-your-award>
Lastly, we ask that you also notify us if you are receiving or expect to receive aid that is not contained in this award offer.
If you have any questions or concerns, please contact our office.
Sincerely,
MSOE Financial Aid Office 414-277-7223 finaid@msoe.edu<mailto:finaid@msoe.edu>
It is the student's responsibility to ensure that his/her contact information on file is accurate: Thomas Hill 606 GREENWAY TER HARTLAND, Wisconsin 53029 * If this address is incorrect, please update it on your my.msoe.edu account.

helpdesk-note.body:
Merged from ticket 7971 Subject: Computers for summer course Description:
Afternoon Helpdesk,
Mark Hoelzer here - from the MSOE Center for BioMolecular Modeling on the 2nd floor of the CC-buildling (room 202). We are hosting an upcoming summer workshop from June 2nd through June 4th on 3d printing. I have about a half dozen desktop 3D printers I want to demonstrate during this workshop and was hoping IT could provide us with 6 laptops to use with these printers. They don't need to be anything special and we would only need them for the three days of the course (and maybe a day or two earlier if possible so we can prepare and set up the work stations).
Is this possible? How can I go about getting these laptops for a short time?
Thanks as always!
-Mark

[MSOE Logo][Milwaukee School of Engineering]<http://www.msoe.edu>
Hello Michelle,
The password for your MSOE account (roubikm@msoe.edu<mailto:roubikm@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 05/25/2016. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 05/25/2016 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters * Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items: * Uppercase letter * Lowercase letter * A number * A symbol Note: The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu> if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.​
Thank you, The MSOE Help Desk (414) 277-7288
This email was sent by an automated process.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Kim, Fanmon and Mary Jo,
I can see from our records that Fanmon changed his password on the 16th, so that would explain why he has been having problems with his account for two weeks. I have no records of any attempts to resolve any email problems in our ticketing database.
Outlook 2013 does a bad job of updating credentials after a password change. All IT workers deal with this problem many times a day, so we could walk Fanmon through this over the phone if he desires. I will include directions here.
Go to Start Menu, in the search bar type "Cred". Click on "Credential Manager". Near the bottom you should see "Generic Credentials". Click on each of these credentials and then click on "Remove from Vault". This will remove the bad password from the saved credentials. Re-open Outlook. Enter your current password into the password field. Your email will then connect. The problem with Blackboard is most likely due to Chrome (or whatever browser you use) having inaccurate (old) credentials saved. Try blackboard in another browser to see if this is the issue. We can give more specific directions if we know which browser you use, but the general idea is:
Clear saved passwords from your browser, clear cache from your browser. Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Kim, Fanmon and Mary Jo,

I can see from our records that Fanmon changed his password on the 16th, so that would explain why he has been having problems with his account for two weeks. I have no records of any attempts to resolve any email problems in our ticketing database. 

Outlook 2013 does a bad job of updating credentials after a password change. All IT workers deal with this problem many times a day, so we could walk Fanmon through this over the phone if he desires. I will include directions here. 
  • Go to Start Menu, in the search bar type "Cred". Click on "Credential Manager". Near the bottom you should see "Generic Credentials". Click on each of these credentials and then click on "Remove from Vault". This will remove the bad password from the saved credentials. Re-open Outlook. Enter your current password into the password field. Your email will then connect. 
The problem with Blackboard is most likely due to Chrome (or whatever browser you use) having inaccurate (old) credentials saved. Try blackboard in another browser to see if this is the issue. We can give more specific directions if we know which browser you use, but the general idea is:
  • Clear saved passwords from your browser, clear cache from your browser. 
Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Re: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I have attended MSOE for over 5 years as a part time student, and am graduating with my Bachelor's degree tomorrow. Am I entitled to keep my laptop? I turned it back in Wednesday night, but would be very interested if this program is extended to me as well.
Thanks,
Brian Burhop
________________________________ From: Helpdesk Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:21 PM Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
[cid:image003.png@01D1AAAD.C24E4AB0]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu
CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p

If I am a part time student graduating, am I able to get a laptop for ownership?
I have been renting them the past years, but didn't have one this quarter.
Thanks!
D. Eyton Zelazo
On Fri, May 27, 2016 at 2:21 PM, Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>> wrote:
[cid:image003.png@01D1AAAD.C24E4AB0]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288<tel:%28414%29277-7288> helpdesk.msoe.edu<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu>
CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Alumni Email Account
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I was wondering when we would have the opportunity to transfer our current email addresses over to @alumni.msoe.edu addresses? Also, is it possible to have email forwarded from our current email to this new email?
I have a number of conversations I don't want to loose if I suddenly loose access to my email account.
Thank you,
Evan Schilling
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

I was wondering when we would have the opportunity to transfer our current email addresses over to @alumni.msoe.edu addresses? Also, is it possible to have email forwarded from our current email to this new email?

I have a number of conversations I don't want to loose if I suddenly loose access to my email account.

Thank you,
Evan Schilling

helpdesk-note.body:
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8626
Hi Evan
You do have the ability to forward all future emails from your MSOE email to your new MSOE alumni email or any other email that you choose. Here is a guide for that process using outlook web-mail. https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Forward-email-to-another-email-account-1ed4ee1e-74f8-4f53-a174-86b748ff6a0e
For saving you past emails there are two methods that you can use to save the emails. You can forward everything that you have in your inbox to your new email account, or you can export all of the data that is in your inbox in a file called a .PST file. Here is a guide on how to do that. https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Export-or-backup-email-contacts-and-calendar-to-an-Outlook-pst-file-14252b52-3075-4e9b-be4e-ff9ef1068f91
Please let us know if you have any more issues.
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Even,
If you haven't already, you can go to this link to create your MSOE alumni email account. Note that our database needs confirmation from the Registrar's office data base that you officially have a date degree conferred in order for our system to create your new email. Registrar's has a process for doing this which takes some time. Don't be too worried if the email account fails to create, if it does fail it just means that your account hasn't been updated by Registrar's yet. Let me know if you have any further questions.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8626

Hi Brian Wenninger, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8627
Since you have graduated, the laptop needs to be gifted so that it is accurately represented as being your property, and no longer MSOE's property. Part of this process does require the wipe, as our software cannot be applied to non-MSOE property. If, as a graduate student, you do need MSOE software for your classes you are able to rent a laptop on a per quarter basis which will allow access to our software. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however, I have attached the hours for the MSOE IT Helpdesk below for your convenience. Please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
Monday - Friday - 8:00 AM - 4:30 PM
Thanks,

On Fri, May 27, 2016 at 2:21 PM, Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu> wrote:


 
Congratulations!


My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.

As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th.  Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed.    If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner.  Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma. 

Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done.  Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining.  The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop. 

Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.

MSOE Technology Program

No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
 
MSOE IT Helpdesk

CC Great Room

helpdesk-note.body:
Yeah it does seem pretty weird, honestly I don't know enough about the specifics to paint you a better picture. I do know where you are coming from and waiting for your new computer is probably the best solution. However in the mean time if you do need to access those applications you can always open up office 365 in your web browser, from there you sign in using MSOE's single sign on portal. This way you can still use those applications online. Same thing with box.com if you need to edit current documents on your computer just throw them into your box account and open them within box. Box allows you to edit these files and save them on your account. If you are interested in following this route I can give you further information or just run by your office to show you in person.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dane Jones, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8673
Below are the instructions for mapping the network drive if restarting the machine does not solve the issue. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
1) Select the Start Button in the bottom left, and select My Computer 2) Select Map A Network Drive 3) From the drop drown labeled Drive Select "O:" 4) For the folder, enter "\\filestore.msoe.edu\Department" 5) Select "Reconnect at login" check box 6) If prompted, enter your MSOE credentials
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Dane Jones,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8673

Below are the instructions for mapping the network drive if restarting the machine does not solve the issue. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.

1) Select the Start Button in the bottom left, and select My Computer
2) Select Map A Network Drive
3) From the drop drown labeled Drive Select "O:"
4) For the folder, enter "\\filestore.msoe.edu\Department"
5) Select "Reconnect at login" check box
6) If prompted, enter your MSOE credentials

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Kyle Davis, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8680
The most common issue that would cause this is an old password for yoru outlook account.
Follow the steps below in order to deleted the stored old outlook password.
Click the Start button and type-in "Credential Manager". A dialogue box should appear. In the dialogue box, under "Generic Credentials", click the vault that contains the outlook credentials. Click Remove from vault. Hit 'yes' when it asks for the confirmation to delete those credentials. Reopen Outlook. Now you should get a pop-up window asking you to enter your credentials.
Once you enter your current password, your Outlook should get connected to Microsoft Exchange and your inbox should get updated with recent emails.Does this solve your issue?
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.description:

Corey Pruess
________________________________ From: Helpdesk Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 1:21:25 PM Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
[cid:image003.png@01D1AAAD.C24E4AB0]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu
CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p

helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Outlook not connecting after password change

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Lukie,
If you have saved your outlook password on your computer you will have to change those credentials saved on your computer. Here are the steps to manage those credentials that could be causing your outlook to not work.
1) Go to start menu. 2) Search "credential manager" 3) within credential manager on the bottom of the page look for "General Credentials" 4) Click the down arrow on the line that reads "MS.Outlook.15:christie@msoe.edu" 5)Now click the link below your credentials to edit them.
This is about all you need to know on how to update your saved outlook credentials. Let me know if you need any further assistance or a deeper explanation.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8693
Outlook not connecting after password change
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Lukie,


If you have saved your outlook password on your computer you will have to change those credentials saved on your computer. Here are the steps to manage those credentials that could be causing your outlook to not work.

4) Click the down arrow on the line that reads "MS.Outlook.15:christie@msoe.edu"
5)Now click the link below your credentials to edit them. 

This is about all you need to know on how to update your saved outlook credentials. Let me know if you need any further assistance or a deeper explanation.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Fw: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I was hoping someone could respond regard my question below on the Laptop Gifting program. Otherwise, could you provide the name of the person that I should contact?
Kind regards,
Brian Burhop
________________________________ From: Burhop, Brian Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:28 PM To: Helpdesk Subject: Re: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
I have attended MSOE for over 5 years as a part time student, and am graduating with my Bachelor's degree tomorrow. Am I entitled to keep my laptop? I turned it back in Wednesday night, but would be very interested if this program is extended to me as well.
Thanks,
Brian Burhop
________________________________ From: Helpdesk Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:21 PM Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
[cid:image003.png@01D1AAAD.C24E4AB0]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu
CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p
